1
00:00:09,767 --> 00:00:14,333
<i>Is it okay if I don't go back to
work after my maternity leave?</i>

2
00:00:14,467 --> 00:00:16,833
<i>Thea's been handling
your accounts well anyway.</i>

3
00:00:16,967 --> 00:00:18,000
<i> I just want to be careful.</i>

4
00:00:18,133 --> 00:00:20,133
<i>She's nice when
she's in front of me.</i>

5
00:00:20,267 --> 00:00:23,633
<i>I just don't know what she does
behind my back.</i>

6
00:00:23,767 --> 00:00:25,267
<i>I'm pregnant,
and you're the father.</i>

7
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:27,467
<i>Thea's been acting differently.</i>

8
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:29,833
<i> Whatever Thea's going through,</i>

9
00:00:29,967 --> 00:00:31,400
<i>I'm sure she'll tell you
eventually.</i>

10
00:00:31,533 --> 00:00:33,467
<i>I just hope she's not hiding
anything from me.</i>

11
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:35,100
<i>We're getting a paternity test.</i>

12
00:00:35,267 --> 00:00:38,533
<i>This was one huge mistake,
one I completely regret.</i>

13
00:00:38,667 --> 00:00:41,133
<i>The baby I'm carrying
is a Torrecampo.</i>

14
00:00:41,267 --> 00:00:43,267
<i>So you're going to take
responsibility.</i>

15
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:44,900
<i>And you're going to acknowledge
this child.</i>

16
00:00:50,733 --> 00:00:53,067
He wouldn't eat at a restaurant
if it were only 30 minutes,

17
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:54,067
right?

18
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:55,533
And if he were meeting a client,

19
00:00:55,667 --> 00:00:57,667
it should take longer than
30 minutes.

20
00:00:59,033 --> 00:01:00,700
Oh my gosh, Yolly.

21
00:01:00,833 --> 00:01:02,800
What do you think Sir Paolo
was doing there?

22
00:01:02,933 --> 00:01:04,933
And who do you think he met?

23
00:01:05,067 --> 00:01:07,000
He didn't even let me inside.

24
00:01:07,167 --> 00:01:10,500
Maybe he didn't want me to see
who he was meeting.

25
00:01:11,900 --> 00:01:13,100
Yolly...

26
00:01:13,233 --> 00:01:16,367
what if Sir Paolo's going back
to his old ways?

27
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:17,733
What if he's seeing another
woman?

28
00:01:17,867 --> 00:01:19,833
That's right, maybe there's
another woman.

29
00:01:23,067 --> 00:01:24,967
Excuse me, Oscar.

30
00:01:25,100 --> 00:01:26,833
What do you think?

31
00:01:26,967 --> 00:01:29,300
You should know better than
anyone, right?

32
00:01:29,433 --> 00:01:31,700
Aren't you like that, too?

33
00:01:31,833 --> 00:01:32,967
Hey!

34
00:01:33,100 --> 00:01:34,067
Why am I getting dragged
into this?

35
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:36,700
I'm just minding my own
business here!

36
00:01:36,833 --> 00:01:38,333
Hey, what is wrong with you two?

37
00:01:38,467 --> 00:01:39,733
Stop it.

38
00:01:40,833 --> 00:01:44,000
Both of you, just keep quiet
for now.

39
00:01:44,133 --> 00:01:48,233
We don't even know what really
happened yet.

40
00:01:48,367 --> 00:01:53,167
And let's not do anything that
could harm our employers, okay?

41
00:01:53,300 --> 00:01:56,267
Now focus on Miss Regina's
event tomorrow.

42
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:59,133
There's still so much
to prepare!

43
00:01:59,267 --> 00:02:00,167
Move it!

44
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:54,133
As long as we hit our target,

45
00:02:54,267 --> 00:02:57,033
two months before the end
of the year,

46
00:02:57,167 --> 00:02:58,700
we'll have a very merry
Christmas.

47
00:03:00,267 --> 00:03:02,800
<i>- Exciting.
- Well, that's all for now.</i>

48
00:03:02,933 --> 00:03:04,833
I won't keep you any longer.

49
00:03:04,967 --> 00:03:08,433
You all need to prepare for the
birthday charity event tonight.

50
00:03:09,567 --> 00:03:10,933
You're all going, right?

51
00:03:11,067 --> 00:03:12,033
- Of course.
- Yes, of course.

52
00:03:12,167 --> 00:03:13,033
Great.

53
00:03:13,167 --> 00:03:14,133
Meeting's over.

54
00:03:15,167 --> 00:03:16,500
Thank you, Sir.

55
00:03:25,833 --> 00:03:26,767
Dad.

56
00:03:26,900 --> 00:03:27,767
Yes, Paolo?

57
00:03:30,667 --> 00:03:31,533
Problem?

58
00:03:35,367 --> 00:03:38,300
There's a very big problem.

59
00:03:41,100 --> 00:03:42,267
Then speak.

60
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:47,467
Thea is pregnant.

61
00:03:49,900 --> 00:03:51,433
I'm going to be
a grandfather again?

62
00:03:52,467 --> 00:03:55,500
Edward's going to be a father?

63
00:03:55,667 --> 00:03:56,967
What's the problem?

64
00:04:00,533 --> 00:04:02,500
Edward isn't the father.

65
00:04:05,533 --> 00:04:06,500
I am.

66
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,667
The nerve!

67
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:18,867
He treats my baby and me
like we're trash,

68
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:22,233
when he's the real trash
for cheating on his wife!

69
00:04:22,367 --> 00:04:24,000
Exactly.

70
00:04:24,133 --> 00:04:26,367
So don't follow his orders.

71
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:29,467
I'm not going to let him
treat me like that.

72
00:04:29,633 --> 00:04:30,833
I'm a Villareal.

73
00:04:30,967 --> 00:04:33,100
I'm not someone you can just
push around.

74
00:04:33,233 --> 00:04:35,267
Hey, nice.

75
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:39,267
But what if they offer you
millions to keep quiet?

76
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:41,033
<i> Like in those movies we watch?</i>

77
00:04:41,167 --> 00:04:45,033
What if they send you abroad
to give birth...

78
00:04:45,167 --> 00:04:48,167
and then take the baby from you?

79
00:04:48,300 --> 00:04:49,900
Sorry.

80
00:04:50,033 --> 00:04:52,433
They can't keep me away
from them.

81
00:04:53,833 --> 00:04:56,333
I'll destroy them first...

82
00:04:56,467 --> 00:04:58,333
before they try to control me.

83
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,333
What were you thinking!

84
00:05:03,067 --> 00:05:06,267
I did not raise you to be stupid
and careless!

85
00:05:11,933 --> 00:05:13,533
Do you have any idea...

86
00:05:15,067 --> 00:05:18,667
how big this scandal
is going to be?

87
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:22,300
Do you know what this will do
to our name once it comes out?

88
00:05:22,433 --> 00:05:24,733
It will ruin our family!

89
00:05:26,567 --> 00:05:28,500
I know, Dad, I know.

90
00:05:30,267 --> 00:05:31,700
I made a mistake.

91
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,633
And you, of all people,
were supposed to be smarter,

92
00:05:35,767 --> 00:05:37,433
than Edward.

93
00:05:37,567 --> 00:05:39,433
Now look at you...

94
00:05:39,567 --> 00:05:42,233
acting like an idiot
over your sex drive!

95
00:05:44,933 --> 00:05:46,367
I'm sorry.

96
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:50,600
It was just one moment
of weakness.

97
00:05:51,933 --> 00:05:53,233
Marj was pregnant,

98
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:55,667
sensitive.

99
00:05:56,900 --> 00:05:57,967
And I was...

100
00:05:59,333 --> 00:06:00,833
Dad, I was weak.

101
00:06:00,967 --> 00:06:03,367
I don't have a weak son!

102
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:04,900
Fix this, Paolo!

103
00:06:05,033 --> 00:06:06,400
Fix it!

104
00:06:06,533 --> 00:06:09,867
Terminate the pregnancy
if you have to!

105
00:06:10,033 --> 00:06:11,200
Dad, no!

106
00:06:12,967 --> 00:06:14,300
The child did nothing wrong.

107
00:06:14,433 --> 00:06:16,300
I won't do that.

108
00:06:16,433 --> 00:06:18,767
And Thea would never agree
to it.

109
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:22,100
That would just
make things worse!

110
00:06:22,233 --> 00:06:24,733
Then how are you going
to clean up this mess?

111
00:06:27,500 --> 00:06:28,600
<i> Well,</i>

112
00:06:29,733 --> 00:06:32,167
I just happen
to be attending a...

113
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:35,067
Torrecampo charity event
tonight.

114
00:06:36,233 --> 00:06:37,800
That's where I'll expose...

115
00:06:37,933 --> 00:06:41,667
everything that happened
between Paolo and me.

116
00:06:41,833 --> 00:06:43,400
That he's the father...

117
00:06:43,533 --> 00:06:45,900
of my baby.

118
00:06:46,033 --> 00:06:49,167
With the paternity test results
to prove it.

119
00:06:49,300 --> 00:06:52,867
Really?

120
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:57,633
Since he's throwing me away,
we all go down together.

121
00:06:58,867 --> 00:07:06,267
I'll make sure his wife and
his family throw him away, too.

122
00:07:16,333 --> 00:07:19,567
Ma'am Regina, thank you so much
for all of this.

123
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:21,300
And happy birthday to you.

124
00:07:21,433 --> 00:07:23,633
Oh, please, we have been doing
this for years.

125
00:07:23,767 --> 00:07:26,800
You know this is what makes
my birthday meaningful.

126
00:07:26,933 --> 00:07:29,000
So thank you all.

127
00:07:29,133 --> 00:07:31,967
Go ahead and enjoy, and make
sure the kids get fed, okay?

128
00:07:32,100 --> 00:07:33,067
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Thank you.

129
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:35,833
Okay.

130
00:07:35,967 --> 00:07:37,333
Hey!

131
00:07:38,967 --> 00:07:40,067
Hi!

132
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:42,200
Thank you so much for coming.

133
00:07:42,333 --> 00:07:43,700
Thank you for inviting us.

134
00:07:43,833 --> 00:07:46,767
Of course, it would not be
complete without you.

135
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:48,667
Thank you, thank you.

136
00:07:48,833 --> 00:07:50,400
Please, sit down, eat.

137
00:07:50,533 --> 00:07:52,067
I'll join you later.

138
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:56,367
Marj.

139
00:07:58,967 --> 00:08:02,833
Just make sure your brother
doesn't cause any trouble, okay?

140
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:08,200
He's in the room with my mom.

141
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:13,267
Enjoy.

142
00:08:24,100 --> 00:08:25,167
What's wrong?

143
00:08:28,367 --> 00:08:30,767
I was just thinking
about your mom.

144
00:08:32,033 --> 00:08:37,433
She does all these charity
events and helps kids.

145
00:08:37,567 --> 00:08:42,367
But she treats Jobert like my
brother is not a good person.

146
00:08:44,367 --> 00:08:47,067
He's always wanted to join
events like this.

147
00:08:48,767 --> 00:08:50,533
Just try to understand mom.

148
00:08:50,667 --> 00:08:51,667
She's just pressured.

149
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:55,067
She wants this event
to be perfect for the press.

150
00:08:55,233 --> 00:08:56,933
She'll soften up with Jobert
eventually.

151
00:09:03,133 --> 00:09:04,467
Hi, Marj!

152
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:05,867
Hi, Paolo!

153
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:08,533
- Hi, Thea.
- Are we late?

154
00:09:08,667 --> 00:09:10,033
You're actually early.

155
00:09:10,167 --> 00:09:12,633
I thought you and Edward
were not coming.

156
00:09:12,767 --> 00:09:13,800
There was heavy traffic.

157
00:09:13,933 --> 00:09:15,967
But of course,
we didn't want to miss this.

158
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:18,267
We've been looking forward
to this.

159
00:09:21,300 --> 00:09:24,233
Sorry, I need to do something,
I forgot something over there.

160
00:09:24,367 --> 00:09:25,333
I'll be back.

161
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:28,300
Excuse me.

162
00:09:35,433 --> 00:09:36,633
Typical.

163
00:09:36,767 --> 00:09:39,333
As usual, the moment I arrive,
he avoids me.

164
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:56,400
Love?

165
00:09:56,533 --> 00:10:00,800
Why didn't you greet
Thea and Edward earlier?

166
00:10:00,967 --> 00:10:05,600
Mom asked me to attend
to some VIP guests.

167
00:10:05,733 --> 00:10:06,833
Of course,

168
00:10:06,967 --> 00:10:08,767
I had to welcome them and...

169
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:10,500
entertain them for a bit.

170
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:14,500
Is that really the reason?

171
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:18,500
What else would it be?

172
00:10:18,633 --> 00:10:22,533
Because honestly, I can tell
something's bothering you.

173
00:10:22,667 --> 00:10:24,567
You're not at ease.

174
00:10:24,700 --> 00:10:26,667
What? No.

175
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:29,867
Love, I want to help you.

176
00:10:31,367 --> 00:10:35,100
But how can I do that
if you won't open up to me?

177
00:10:36,567 --> 00:10:39,500
So tell me.

178
00:10:39,633 --> 00:10:41,567
What's really bothering you?

179
00:10:49,667 --> 00:10:50,633
<i> Love...</i>

180
00:10:53,167 --> 00:10:55,733
I was actually planning
to tell you.

181
00:11:01,767 --> 00:11:03,100
The truth is...

182
00:11:04,167 --> 00:11:06,400
Good evening, everyone.

183
00:11:06,533 --> 00:11:08,367
I'm Thea Villareal.

184
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:12,400
Edward's girlfriend,

185
00:11:12,533 --> 00:11:15,167
son of Mom Regina.

186
00:11:15,300 --> 00:11:20,300
I'm here to greet Mom Regina
a very, very happy birthday.

187
00:11:20,433 --> 00:11:22,233
Thank you, Thea.

188
00:11:22,367 --> 00:11:24,467
Thank you, thank you.

189
00:11:27,033 --> 00:11:29,867
And thank you so much
for already accepting me...

190
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:32,733
- as one of your own.
- Of course.

191
00:11:34,267 --> 00:11:37,300
Because the truth is...

192
00:11:37,433 --> 00:11:41,233
being a Torrecampo...

193
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:42,833
already runs in my blood.

194
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:51,933
Because in my womb...

195
00:11:52,067 --> 00:11:59,600
is Mom Regina and Daddy Greg's
second grandchild.

196
00:11:59,733 --> 00:12:03,433
Wow, congratulations, Thea!

197
00:12:03,567 --> 00:12:05,400
<i> Yes,</i>

198
00:12:05,533 --> 00:12:06,900
I'm pregnant.

199
00:12:09,700 --> 00:12:11,100
And he's the father.

200
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:37,367
Yes.

201
00:12:45,700 --> 00:12:47,133
That's right.

202
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:48,800
I'm going to be a dad!

203
00:12:56,667 --> 00:12:58,000
Sorry, sorry, everyone.

204
00:12:58,133 --> 00:13:01,700
Mom, Dad, we had to announce
the good news here.

205
00:13:01,833 --> 00:13:04,867
The truth is, when Thea told me,

206
00:13:06,333 --> 00:13:08,533
I was so happy,
I couldn't contain myself.

207
00:13:09,100 --> 00:13:11,200
So, Mom...

208
00:13:11,333 --> 00:13:13,967
this is our birthday gift
for you.

209
00:13:16,667 --> 00:13:19,033
- I'm happy for you!
- Thank you!

210
00:13:19,167 --> 00:13:21,000
You're going to be a dad!

211
00:13:21,167 --> 00:13:23,000
Thank you, thank you.

212
00:13:24,433 --> 00:13:26,967
This is the best birthday ever.

213
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:29,567
Best birthday gift for me!

214
00:13:36,567 --> 00:13:39,200
Congratulations!

215
00:13:40,667 --> 00:13:42,733
Love, are you okay?

216
00:13:42,867 --> 00:13:45,133
Why are you so quiet?

217
00:13:45,267 --> 00:13:47,267
Aren't you happy for them?

218
00:13:50,067 --> 00:13:51,833
Of course, I'm happy.

219
00:13:51,967 --> 00:13:53,867
I'm just surprised
by their good news, too.

220
00:13:55,733 --> 00:13:57,700
Come on,
let's congratulate them.

221
00:13:59,233 --> 00:14:01,133
But, sorry.

222
00:14:01,267 --> 00:14:02,533
My bad.

223
00:14:02,667 --> 00:14:05,100
What were you about
to tell me earlier?

224
00:14:05,233 --> 00:14:07,867
Go ahead, finish it.

225
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,767
Actually, Love,

226
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:14,700
I just wanted to say sorry
for making you worry.

227
00:14:14,833 --> 00:14:15,833
The truth is,

228
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:20,500
work has just really been
getting to me.

229
00:14:20,633 --> 00:14:22,133
That's it.

230
00:14:22,267 --> 00:14:24,400
You don't have to worry anymore.

231
00:14:24,533 --> 00:14:28,367
Love, if this is about work,
just tell me.

232
00:14:28,533 --> 00:14:31,000
Maybe I can help.

233
00:14:31,133 --> 00:14:34,000
Love, I don't want to add
to your stress.

234
00:14:34,133 --> 00:14:37,767
I know you already have
your hands full with our baby.

235
00:14:37,900 --> 00:14:40,767
I don't want you worrying
about me, too, okay?

236
00:14:40,900 --> 00:14:42,900
I can handle this.

237
00:14:43,033 --> 00:14:44,800
Let's just enjoy the event,
okay.

238
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:48,267
Come on,

239
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:49,800
let's congratulate them.

240
00:14:52,333 --> 00:14:55,200
Paolo and Marjorie, join us,
come on.

241
00:14:55,333 --> 00:14:56,400
So we're complete

242
00:14:56,533 --> 00:14:57,800
- for the picture.
- Marj!

243
00:14:57,933 --> 00:14:59,733
- Congratulations!
- Were you surprised?

244
00:14:59,867 --> 00:15:01,500
Congratulations!

245
00:15:01,667 --> 00:15:05,000
We're both moms now.

246
00:15:05,133 --> 00:15:06,700
Congratulations.

247
00:15:38,267 --> 00:15:39,833
<i> I'm relieved.</i>

248
00:15:39,967 --> 00:15:42,467
But I don't understand, Dad.

249
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:45,067
Thea warned me she was pregnant.

250
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:48,800
And then, suddenly,
she announced at the party...

251
00:15:48,933 --> 00:15:50,667
that she's pregnant
with Edward's baby.

252
00:15:52,467 --> 00:15:53,367
Why?

253
00:16:00,700 --> 00:16:02,233
Because I told her to.

254
00:16:04,833 --> 00:16:05,800
You did?

255
00:16:07,700 --> 00:16:08,767
How?

256
00:16:13,033 --> 00:16:14,233
<i> Come in.</i>

257
00:16:18,333 --> 00:16:19,433
<i> Daddy Greg,</i>

258
00:16:20,867 --> 00:16:24,600
<i> you sent for me?</i>

259
00:16:24,733 --> 00:16:26,100
<i> Come in.</i>

260
00:16:26,233 --> 00:16:28,233
<i>I don't want you getting
stressed...</i>

261
00:16:28,367 --> 00:16:29,933
<i> standing up.</i>

262
00:16:30,067 --> 00:16:31,667
<i> It might affect the baby.</i>

263
00:16:35,233 --> 00:16:38,600
<i>- You know about...
- Of course I do.</i>

264
00:16:38,733 --> 00:16:41,400
<i>Nothing gets past me
in this house.</i>

265
00:16:41,567 --> 00:16:42,467
<i> Come.</i>

266
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:43,567
<i> Sit.</i>

267
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:04,533
<i>So Paolo already told you
about our agreement?</i>

268
00:17:05,567 --> 00:17:06,567
<i> Agreement?</i>

269
00:17:10,867 --> 00:17:12,367
<i> But,</i>

270
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:14,467
<i> there was nothing agreed upon.</i>

271
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:15,667
<i> Was there?</i>

272
00:17:21,667 --> 00:17:24,433
<i>You wanted to broadcast
to the whole world...</i>

273
00:17:24,567 --> 00:17:26,233
<i>that he's the father
of your child.</i>

274
00:17:28,100 --> 00:17:29,600
<i>And he wanted you to keep
your mouth shut.</i>

275
00:17:32,133 --> 00:17:34,700
<i>He offered to financially
support the child.</i>

276
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:38,200
<i> You were asking for much more.</i>

277
00:17:40,167 --> 00:17:42,867
<i>I'm just demanding
what I deserve.</i>

278
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:52,533
<i> You think you deserve Paolo...</i>

279
00:17:53,833 --> 00:17:55,267
<i> when you already have Edward?</i>

280
00:17:58,667 --> 00:18:00,933
<i> I deserve for my child...</i>

281
00:18:01,067 --> 00:18:02,133
<i> to have a father.</i>

282
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:04,667
<i> A real father.</i>

283
00:18:06,100 --> 00:18:09,567
<i>Money alone won't fill
what we need.</i>

284
00:18:12,067 --> 00:18:14,067
<i> I admire your grit, dear.</i>

285
00:18:15,367 --> 00:18:17,233
<i> You want the best.</i>

286
00:18:17,367 --> 00:18:18,367
<i> I get it.</i>

287
00:18:20,233 --> 00:18:22,033
<i>But you can't have
what you want.</i>

288
00:18:29,333 --> 00:18:31,533
<i>How are you going to benefit
from our name...</i>

289
00:18:32,867 --> 00:18:35,700
<i>if you destroy it before you
even become part of it?</i>

290
00:18:39,867 --> 00:18:41,533
<i> But in my defense,</i>

291
00:18:41,667 --> 00:18:44,433
<i>I won't let anyone destroy
my family.</i>

292
00:18:47,733 --> 00:18:49,133
<i> Our family.</i>

293
00:18:51,833 --> 00:18:53,600
<i> Someone would have to die...</i>

294
00:18:53,733 --> 00:18:54,867
<i> before that happens.</i>

295
00:18:56,067 --> 00:18:57,033
<i> Okay?</i>

296
00:18:58,967 --> 00:19:01,133
<i>So here's what's going
to happen.</i>

297
00:19:01,267 --> 00:19:03,667
<i>You're going to say Edward
is the father of the baby.</i>

298
00:19:04,833 --> 00:19:05,800
<i> That way,</i>

299
00:19:07,333 --> 00:19:10,167
<i>the child will still be
a legitimate Torrecampo.</i>

300
00:19:13,033 --> 00:19:14,167
<i> He'll definitely...</i>

301
00:19:15,400 --> 00:19:17,100
<i> ask you to marry him.</i>

302
00:19:19,633 --> 00:19:21,067
<i> And you're going to say yes.</i>

303
00:19:24,700 --> 00:19:26,933
<i>But what if I don't want
to marry him?</i>

304
00:19:29,367 --> 00:19:32,833
<i>I don't even know
if he can provide for us.</i>

305
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:38,233
<i> Edward may be an idiot,</i>

306
00:19:38,367 --> 00:19:40,867
<i> but he's still a Torrecampo.</i>

307
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:43,133
<i> He'll never be broke.</i>

308
00:19:43,267 --> 00:19:47,500
<i>I'll finance his stupid
start-up...</i>

309
00:19:47,633 --> 00:19:50,267
<i>to make sure your family
is financially secure.</i>

310
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:51,867
<i> And in return,</i>

311
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:55,700
<i>you have to promise me that you
will never go near Paolo again.</i>

312
00:19:57,800 --> 00:20:00,867
<i>And the identity
of the real father...</i>

313
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:02,733
<i> stays a secret, forever.</i>

314
00:20:20,767 --> 00:20:23,200
<i> How could you do this, Dad?</i>

315
00:20:23,333 --> 00:20:26,800
I already betrayed Edward by
getting his girlfriend pregnant.

316
00:20:26,933 --> 00:20:28,367
And now we're going to make him
take responsibility

317
00:20:28,500 --> 00:20:30,467
for my child?

318
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:32,233
That's so unfair to him!

319
00:20:35,267 --> 00:20:36,233
Then...

320
00:20:38,100 --> 00:20:40,600
you shouldn't have been unfair
to him...

321
00:20:41,633 --> 00:20:44,300
when you slept with his
girlfriend in the first place.

322
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:50,300
Don't give me that look.

323
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:52,367
<i> Don't.</i>

324
00:20:55,933 --> 00:20:56,900
What do you want?

325
00:20:57,933 --> 00:20:59,200
To lose your family?

326
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:02,500
Our family?

327
00:21:02,633 --> 00:21:04,433
Think of it this way.

328
00:21:04,567 --> 00:21:06,800
You're doing your brother
a favor.

329
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:10,200
You're sparing him the pain...

330
00:21:10,333 --> 00:21:12,433
of knowing about your betrayal
with Thea.

331
00:21:17,867 --> 00:21:20,733
But, Dad,
that's not fair to him.

332
00:21:22,833 --> 00:21:24,733
Make a choice.

333
00:21:24,867 --> 00:21:26,033
Your conscience?

334
00:21:26,167 --> 00:21:29,833
Or Marj and your child?

335
00:21:43,700 --> 00:21:44,700
My wife.

336
00:21:48,033 --> 00:21:49,433
I choose my wife...

337
00:21:51,333 --> 00:21:52,433
and my child.

338
00:21:56,433 --> 00:21:58,567
Then you chose wisely, my son.

339
00:22:04,367 --> 00:22:06,700
Thank you, Ma'am Regina,
for visiting.

340
00:22:07,133 --> 00:22:08,567
We were really surprised.

341
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:11,267
Your donation is so generous.

342
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:14,600
Oh, it's just a portion
of the funds we raised

343
00:22:14,733 --> 00:22:17,300
from my birthday
for the orphans.

344
00:22:17,467 --> 00:22:20,133
Since my daughter-in-law's
brother studies here,

345
00:22:20,267 --> 00:22:21,567
I thought...

346
00:22:21,700 --> 00:22:24,100
I'd just add more
to the school's funds.

347
00:22:24,233 --> 00:22:25,733
Thank you again.

348
00:22:25,867 --> 00:22:27,167
You're welcome.

349
00:22:27,300 --> 00:22:29,467
- Happy...
- Jobert, wait!

350
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:30,767
Sweetie, wait!

351
00:22:30,900 --> 00:22:32,033
Hold on!

352
00:22:33,167 --> 00:22:35,433
Hey, careful.

353
00:22:35,567 --> 00:22:37,600
Yolly, why is he running around?

354
00:22:37,733 --> 00:22:40,333
I thought class
was already dismissed?

355
00:22:40,467 --> 00:22:42,700
Ma'am, I'm just taking him
to the playroom.

356
00:22:42,833 --> 00:22:44,367
He'll play for a bit.

357
00:22:44,500 --> 00:22:46,167
It's playtime right now, Ma'am.

358
00:22:46,300 --> 00:22:47,367
Oh, okay.

359
00:22:47,500 --> 00:22:51,067
Just make sure he doesn't
get hurt or trip.

360
00:22:51,233 --> 00:22:54,533
Yolly, he's sweating,
wipe him down.

361
00:22:54,667 --> 00:22:58,633
You're such a wonderful example,
Madam.

362
00:22:58,767 --> 00:23:02,200
It's no surprise Jobert
is such a good student.

363
00:23:02,333 --> 00:23:05,833
He sees you as his role model.

364
00:23:05,967 --> 00:23:07,500
Of course.

365
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:12,967
All right then.

366
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:15,367
Enjoy your playtime.

367
00:23:24,267 --> 00:23:26,367
Wait, I might slip.

368
00:23:26,500 --> 00:23:27,733
Don't worry, I've got you.

369
00:23:27,867 --> 00:23:28,733
Hold on.

370
00:23:28,867 --> 00:23:30,067
What is this?
What are you up to?

371
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:32,133
- Just be patient.
- Straight ahead?

372
00:23:32,267 --> 00:23:33,867
Yes, straight ahead.

373
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:35,867
What is this? Wait a second.

374
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,200
- It's a surprise.
- This is hard.

375
00:23:37,333 --> 00:23:38,833
- I'm wearing high heels.
- Okay, step.

376
00:23:38,967 --> 00:23:41,367
- How many steps?
- Just one, just one.

377
00:23:41,500 --> 00:23:43,667
- Another one?
- One more.

378
00:23:43,800 --> 00:23:45,400
Okay.

379
00:23:45,533 --> 00:23:46,533
What is this?

380
00:23:46,667 --> 00:23:47,900
- Where are we?
- There.

381
00:23:48,033 --> 00:23:50,400
- Straight ahead?
- Straight ahead.

382
00:23:50,533 --> 00:23:52,067
Hey, are you peeking?

383
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:54,833
No! Look, my eyes
are tightly shut.

384
00:23:56,667 --> 00:23:58,900
Here, come, come here.

385
00:23:59,033 --> 00:24:00,167
Here? Here?

386
00:24:00,300 --> 00:24:01,500
- Stop, stop, okay, right there.
- Oh my gosh, what is this?

387
00:24:01,633 --> 00:24:04,467
One moment, no cheating.

388
00:24:04,600 --> 00:24:05,833
- Stay there.
- Are we good?

389
00:24:05,967 --> 00:24:06,967
Wait, wait.

390
00:24:08,167 --> 00:24:09,867
Okay, open your eyes.

391
00:24:13,567 --> 00:24:14,533
Wow!

392
00:24:16,133 --> 00:24:17,600
This place is beautiful.

393
00:24:20,867 --> 00:24:22,267
But it's not as beautiful
as you are.

394
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:28,900
You know, Thea...

395
00:24:29,067 --> 00:24:32,200
I think I'm the happiest man
in the world.

396
00:24:33,867 --> 00:24:35,733
You're my girlfriend...

397
00:24:36,867 --> 00:24:38,300
and we're having a baby.

398
00:24:45,500 --> 00:24:46,467
I guess...

399
00:24:49,333 --> 00:24:52,967
it's still possible for me
to be truly happy...

400
00:24:53,100 --> 00:24:57,700
if you agree to spend the rest
of your life with me.

401
00:25:19,333 --> 00:25:21,033
Thea Villareal,

402
00:25:23,067 --> 00:25:24,267
will you marry me?

403
00:25:36,633 --> 00:25:37,733
So?

404
00:25:38,300 --> 00:25:39,533
Yes.

405
00:25:39,667 --> 00:25:40,767
<i> What?</i>

406
00:25:40,900 --> 00:25:41,667
Yes.

407
00:25:43,933 --> 00:25:45,933
I'll marry you, Edward!

408
00:26:32,133 --> 00:26:36,000
I want to take care
of Baby Jasmine.

409
00:26:36,133 --> 00:26:39,667
Do you really let Jobert
carry my granddaughter?

410
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:42,000
What if he hurts Jasmine?

411
00:26:42,167 --> 00:26:44,033
Do you know he hurt a classmate?

412
00:26:44,167 --> 00:26:46,000
I saw it myself when I visited
his school.

413
00:26:46,133 --> 00:26:47,767
What if he does the same
thing to my granddaughter?

414
00:26:47,900 --> 00:26:49,700
Mom has a right to be concerned.

415
00:26:49,833 --> 00:26:51,500
Jobert might be left alone
with Jasmine.

416
00:26:51,633 --> 00:26:54,367
I know Jobert
isn't really violent,

417
00:26:54,500 --> 00:26:56,067
but it's still not safe.

418
00:26:56,200 --> 00:26:57,833
Marj, where's Jasmine?

419
00:26:57,967 --> 00:26:59,767
She's in the room, Mom,
sleeping.

420
00:26:59,900 --> 00:27:01,233
And who's with her?

421
00:27:01,367 --> 00:27:02,567
Good job, Jobert.

422
00:27:02,700 --> 00:27:05,467
Baby Jasmine's already sleeping.

423
00:27:05,600 --> 00:27:07,300
She's not crying anymore.

424
00:27:11,033 --> 00:27:13,233
Jasmine! My granddaughter!
